sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as RHOAI Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KServeSvc as KServe Service<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant vLLM as vLLM API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant HPU as HPU Device<br/>(Intel Gaudi)
    participant Ray as Ray Head Node<br/>6379/TCP
    participant Worker as HPU Worker (rank N)<br/>HCCL Dynamic
    participant NIXL as NIXL Agent<br/>TCP/RDMA
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Single HPU Inference Request

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Gateway->>KServeSvc: Forward (cluster-internal)<br/>kube-rbac-proxy verified
    KServeSvc->>vLLM: HTTP :8000<br/>No TLS (internal)
    vLLM->>HPU: Model forward pass<br/>HPU driver
    HPU-->>vLLM: Inference result
    vLLM-->>KServeSvc: JSON Response
    KServeSvc-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: Multi-HPU Tensor Parallel Inference

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Gateway->>vLLM: Forward to rank 0<br/>:8000 HTTP
    vLLM->>Ray: Coordinate workers<br/>:6379 TCP plaintext
    Ray->>Worker: Schedule execution
    Worker->>Worker: HCCL all-reduce/all-gather<br/>Dynamic ports, plaintext
    Worker-->>vLLM: Aggregated result
    vLLM-->>Gateway: JSON Response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: KV Cache Disaggregation (NIXL)

    vLLM->>NIXL: Prefill KV cache<br/>TCP/RDMA, plaintext
    NIXL->>Worker: Transfer to decode instance<br/>TCP/RDMA, plaintext
    Worker-->>vLLM: Decode with transferred KV

    Note over Client,S3: Model Loading (Startup)

    vLLM->>S3: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS :443 TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS IAM / SA auth
    S3-->>vLLM: Model artifacts
    vLLM->>HPU: Load model to device memory
